# Microsoft OAuth Configuration (used for Outlook service)
# (Go to https://portal.azure.com/#view/Microsoft_AAD_RegisteredApps/ApplicationsListBlade to register your app)
# 1. Click "New registration"
# 2. Set a name for your application
# 3. Under "Supported account types", select "Accounts in any organizational directory and personal Microsoft accounts"
# 4. Under "Redirect URI", select "Web" and add: http://localhost:8080/api/v1/service-connections/callback/outlook
# 5. After registration, copy the "Application (client) ID" as your MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID
# 6. Go to "Certificates & secrets" -> "New client secret" -> Copy the value as your MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET
# 7. Go to "API permissions" -> "Add a permission" -> "Microsoft Graph" -> "Delegated permissions"
# 8. Add the following permissions: Mail.Read, Mail.Send, Mail.ReadWrite, offline_access
# 9. Click "Grant admin consent" if required by your organization
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=""
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=""

